{
  "stem": "24397.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And some kids came along, and they ripped off my school satchel I used to wear on my back and threw it onto the grass.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and I went over to retrieve it, and there was a policeman standing right by there.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So he grabbed a hold of me, because I trod on the grass and made a big scene about this.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Took down my name, and my parents were called to school.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And the teacher made a big issue about how these Jewish kids have no respect for property and, you know, this tremendous-- big, big thing they made out of that.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And, and just because they pushed everything of mine on there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Eight.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "'38.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Something.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "A strange thing, sometimes a, a sight or a smell can bring things back to you in a rush.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Years later, around 1952, I was a tank commander in the British Army going along at the end of Rhine army maneuvers, going along the little town of Hamley along the River Weser there.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There are all neatly lawns there on the side of the road.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the driver, who used to ask me to translate every sign he saw, asked me, what's that sign down there?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so I said, it's 'keep off the grass.' And as soon-- soon as I saw that, boy, I was transported back in time to that issue.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I remember telling him, right straight on, and we went right over that sign and we dug a trench in that road, must have been about three feet deep.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But it's, it's just an indication how that feeling of kind of frustration and, and anger can well up in you.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It doesn't matter how many years.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
